cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for improving human pose estimation in videos. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves developing a personalized ConvNet pose estimator, which falls under the category of ML and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves using dense optical flow, which is a common technique in multimedia (MM) research, and developing an occlusion-aware self-evaluation model, which could be classified under robotics (RO) research. Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.RO, ordered from most to least likely.
